---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Dev Process — Brian Borg">
  <link slot="head" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />

  <!-- Back link -->
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pt-6">
    <a href="/" class="text-teal-400 hover:text-teal-300 text-sm font-medium transition-colors">&larr; Back to brianborg.com</a>
  </div>

  <!-- HERO -->
  <div class="hero-section relative px-6 md:px-[60px] py-[60px] pb-[50px] border-b border-teal-400/15 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="hero-glow absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="text-[11px] tracking-[0.25em] uppercase text-teal-400 mb-4 font-semibold">Brian Borg's Dev Process Template</div>
      <h1 class="text-[clamp(32px,4vw,52px)] font-bold leading-[1.15] text-white max-w-[700px] mb-3">From Idea to <span class="text-teal-300">Production</span></h1>
      <p class="text-[15px] text-gray-500 max-w-[600px] mb-8">A complete, repeatable development process. One setup script, consistent quality across every project. Built for the AI-assisted development era.</p>
      <div class="flex gap-2.5 flex-wrap">
        <span class="pill-teal">GitHub Actions CI</span>
        <span class="pill-green">80% Coverage Gate</span>
        <span class="pill-purple">Pre-commit Hooks</span>
        <span class="pill-amber">Security Scanning</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- NAV -->
  <nav class="sticky-nav sticky top-0 z-[100] bg-gray-950/95 backdrop-blur-[12px] border-b border-teal-400/15 px-6 md:px-[60px] flex gap-0 overflow-x-auto">
    <button class="nav-btn active" onclick="show('workflow', this)">Daily Workflow</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('branching', this)">Branching</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('ci', this)">CI Pipeline</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('testing', this)">Testing</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('hooks', this)">Pre-commit</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('report', this)">Build Report</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('reviews', this)">Review Gates</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('notify', this)">Notifications</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('dod', this)">Definition of Done</button>
    <button class="nav-btn" onclick="show('toolbox', this)">Full Toolbox</button>
  </nav>

  <!-- DAILY WORKFLOW -->
  <section id="workflow" class="section active">
    <h2 class="text-[28px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-white">Daily <span class="text-teal-300">Workflow</span></h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-9 max-w-[620px]">Eight steps from starting work to clean-up. Every feature, every bug fix, every time.</p>

    <div class="flow">
      <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="flow-num">01</div>
        <div class="flow-body">
          <div class="flow-title">Start from fresh dev</div>
          <div class="flow-desc">Always begin by pulling the latest development branch. Never work from stale code.</div>
          <div class="flow-cmd">git checkout dev && git pull</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="flow-num">02</div>
        <div class="flow-body">
          <div class="flow-title">Create a feature branch</div>
          <div class="flow-desc">Every change gets its own branch. Name it clearly — this becomes the PR title context.</div>
          <div class="flow-cmd">git checkout -b feature/add-audio-extraction</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="flow-num">03</div>
        <div class="flow-body">
          <div class="flow-title">Build the feature</div>
          <div class="flow-desc">Write the code and write the tests in the same branch. Tests are not a follow-up task — they ship with the code, always.</div>
          <div class="flow-note">Never create a separate "add tests later" PR. Code + tests = one unit of work.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="flow-num">04</div>
        <div class="flow-body">
          <div class="flow-title">Verify locally</div>
          <div class="flow-desc">Run the full test suite. Pre-commit hooks check formatting, linting, and secrets automatically on commit.</div>
          <div class="flow-cmd">pytest -v</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="flow-num">05</div>
        <div class="flow-body">
          <div class="flow-title">Push and create PR</div>
          <div class="flow-desc">Push the branch. The PR template auto-fills with what/why/how-to-test/checklist. Fill it out.</div>
          <div class="flow-cmd">git push -u origin feature/add-audio-extraction</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="flow-num">06</div>
        <div class="flow-body">
          <div class="flow-title">CI runs automatically</div>
          <div class="flow-desc">GitHub Actions kicks off three jobs: lint, test, and security scan. All must pass before the PR can merge.</div>
          <div class="flow-note">CI fails if coverage drops below 80% or if formatting/linting issues exist.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="flow-num">07</div>
        <div class="flow-body">
          <div class="flow-title">Merge on GitHub</div>
          <div class="flow-desc">Never merge locally. Always through a PR on GitHub. Update CHANGELOG.md before merging.</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flow-step">
        <div class="flow-num">08</div>
        <div class="flow-body">
          <div class="flow-title">Clean up</div>
          <div class="flow-desc">Switch to main, pull latest, delete merged branches — locally and remotely.</div>
          <div class="flow-cmd">git-done</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- BRANCHING -->
  <section id="branching" class="section">
    <h2 class="text-[28px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-white">Branching <span class="text-teal-300">Strategy</span></h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-9 max-w-[620px]">Three long-lived branches. Short-lived feature branches. PRs flow upward.</p>

    <div class="diagram-box mb-7 max-w-[700px]">
      <div class="branch-row">
        <span class="font-mono text-sm font-medium min-w-[100px] text-green-400">main</span>
        <span class="text-[13px] text-gray-500">Production-ready code. Deploys to production. Always stable.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="branch-row">
        <span class="font-mono text-sm font-medium min-w-[100px] text-amber-400">staging</span>
        <span class="text-[13px] text-gray-500">Pre-production testing. Validates before promotion to main.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="branch-row">
        <span class="font-mono text-sm font-medium min-w-[100px] text-teal-300">dev</span>
        <span class="text-[13px] text-gray-500">Active development. Feature branches merge here first.</span>
      </div>
      <div class="branch-row border-none!">
        <span class="font-mono text-sm font-medium min-w-[100px] text-purple-400">feature/*</span>
        <span class="text-[13px] text-gray-500">Short-lived. One per task. Created from dev, merged back to dev.</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="diagram-box max-w-[500px]">
      <div class="text-[12px] text-teal-400 font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-4">PR Flow Direction</div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm flex-wrap">
        <span class="text-purple-400 font-mono text-[13px]">feature/*</span>
        <span class="text-gray-500">&rarr;</span>
        <span class="text-teal-300 font-mono text-[13px]">dev</span>
        <span class="text-gray-500">&rarr;</span>
        <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-[13px]">staging</span>
        <span class="text-gray-500">&rarr;</span>
        <span class="text-green-400 font-mono text-[13px]">main</span>
      </div>
      <div class="text-[12px] text-gray-500 mt-3">Never develop directly on main, staging, or dev. Always branch.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CI PIPELINE -->
  <section id="ci" class="section">
    <h2 class="text-[28px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-white">CI <span class="text-teal-300">Pipeline</span></h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-9 max-w-[620px]">Three jobs run on every push and every PR. All must pass before merge.</p>

    <div class="ci-pipeline">
      <div class="ci-stage">
        <div class="text-[10px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase font-semibold mb-2.5 text-teal-300">1. Lint</div>
        <ul class="ci-items ci-lint">
          <li>black — formatting check</li>
          <li>ruff — linting + auto-fix</li>
          <li>Fails if code isn't formatted</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ci-stage">
        <div class="text-[10px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase font-semibold mb-2.5 text-green-400">2. Test</div>
        <ul class="ci-items ci-test">
          <li>pytest with coverage</li>
          <li>80% coverage threshold</li>
          <li>HTML report + JUnit XML</li>
          <li>Coverage summary in PR</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ci-stage">
        <div class="text-[10px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase font-semibold mb-2.5 text-amber-400">3. Security</div>
        <ul class="ci-items ci-sec">
          <li>detect-secrets — leaked keys</li>
          <li>pip-audit — dependency CVEs</li>
          <li>bandit — Python code scan</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mb-3.5">CI Outputs</h3>
    <div class="cards-grid max-w-[800px]">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Test Results</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Pass/fail summary on PR checks tab via JUnit XML. Download <code class="text-teal-400 text-xs">reports/test-report.html</code> for full detail.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Coverage Map</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Line-by-line coverage in <code class="text-teal-400 text-xs">reports/coverage/index.html</code>. Summary printed in GitHub Actions job summary.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Security Report</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Python code scan in <code class="text-teal-400 text-xs">reports/bandit-report.json</code>. Dependency vulnerabilities flagged inline.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-4">All artifacts retained for 30 days. Dependabot opens weekly PRs for dependency updates.</div>
  </section>

  <!-- TESTING -->
  <section id="testing" class="section">
    <h2 class="text-[28px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-white">Testing <span class="text-teal-300">Requirements</span></h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-9 max-w-[620px]">Tests ship with code. Always. No exceptions.</p>

    <div class="cards-grid mb-8">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3 text-green-400">+</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">New Feature</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Unit tests + integration tests in the same PR as the feature code.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3 text-red-400">!</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Bug Fix</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Write a test that reproduces the bug first. Then fix the code. Same PR.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3 text-amber-400">~</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Changed Behavior</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Update existing tests to match the new behavior. Same PR.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3 text-gray-500">-</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Removed Feature</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Remove the feature's tests. Don't leave dead tests behind. Same PR.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="diagram-box max-w-[600px]">
      <div class="text-[12px] text-teal-400 font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-5">The Testing Pyramid</div>
      <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-0">
        <div class="w-[30%] py-3.5 text-center bg-purple-400/10 border border-purple-400/30 rounded-t-lg">
          <div class="font-mono text-[13px] font-medium text-purple-400">E2E</div>
          <div class="text-[11px] text-gray-500 mt-0.5">Few — full browser flows</div>
        </div>
        <div class="w-[62%] py-3.5 text-center bg-amber-400/10 border border-amber-400/25 border-t-0">
          <div class="font-mono text-[13px] font-medium text-amber-400">Integration</div>
          <div class="text-[11px] text-gray-500 mt-0.5">Moderate — API-level tests</div>
        </div>
        <div class="w-full py-3.5 text-center bg-green-400/10 border border-green-400/25 border-t-0 rounded-b-lg">
          <div class="font-mono text-[13px] font-medium text-green-400">Unit Tests</div>
          <div class="text-[11px] text-gray-500 mt-0.5">Many — pure logic, fast</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 max-w-[600px] mt-5">
      <strong class="text-gray-100">Quality over percentage.</strong> Prioritize error paths, boundary values, state transitions, and integration points. Don't waste time testing trivial getters or framework internals.
    </div>
    <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 max-w-[600px] mt-2.5">
      <strong class="text-gray-100">Tests are permanent.</strong> They are regression tests. A future change that breaks an old test is the system working correctly.
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PRE-COMMIT HOOKS -->
  <section id="hooks" class="section">
    <h2 class="text-[28px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-white">Pre-commit <span class="text-teal-300">Hooks</span></h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-9 max-w-[620px]">Nine hooks run automatically before every commit. Catches problems before they reach CI.</p>

    <table class="hooks-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Hook</th><th>What It Does</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>trailing-whitespace</td><td>Removes trailing whitespace from all files</td></tr>
        <tr><td>end-of-file-fixer</td><td>Ensures every file ends with a newline</td></tr>
        <tr><td>check-yaml</td><td>Validates YAML syntax (catches CI config errors)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>check-added-large-files</td><td>Blocks files over 500KB from being committed</td></tr>
        <tr><td>check-merge-conflict</td><td>Catches unresolved merge conflict markers</td></tr>
        <tr><td>detect-private-key</td><td>Prevents accidentally committing private keys</td></tr>
        <tr><td>black</td><td>Auto-formats Python code to consistent style</td></tr>
        <tr><td>ruff</td><td>Lints Python code and auto-fixes common issues</td></tr>
        <tr><td>detect-secrets</td><td>Scans for API keys, passwords, and credentials</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <!-- BUILD REPORT -->
  <section id="report" class="section">
    <h2 class="text-[28px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-white">Build <span class="text-teal-300">Report</span></h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-9 max-w-[620px]">Every PR gets a consolidated build report posted as a sticky comment. Updates on each push. Full history preserved.</p>

    <div class="diagram-box max-w-[650px]">
      <div class="text-[12px] text-teal-400 font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-4">What the Build Report Shows</div>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-5">
        <div>
          <div class="text-[13px] font-semibold text-white mb-2">Test Results</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xs leading-8">
            <div><span class="text-green-400">Passed</span> <span class="text-gray-500 float-right">47</span></div>
            <div><span class="text-red-400">Failed</span> <span class="text-gray-500 float-right">2</span></div>
            <div><span class="text-amber-400">Skipped</span> <span class="text-gray-500 float-right">1</span></div>
            <div><span class="text-gray-500">Errors</span> <span class="text-gray-500 float-right">0</span></div>
            <div class="border-t border-teal-400/15 pt-1 mt-1"><span class="text-white">Total</span> <span class="text-gray-100 float-right">50</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-[13px] font-semibold text-white mb-2">Coverage</div>
          <div class="font-mono text-xs leading-8">
            <div><span class="text-gray-100">Overall</span> <span class="text-green-400 float-right">87.3%</span></div>
            <div><span class="text-gray-100">Threshold</span> <span class="text-gray-500 float-right">80%</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="mt-3 text-[11px] text-gray-500">Files below 80% are listed individually with their coverage percentage.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cards-grid max-w-[650px] mt-7">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Sticky PR Comment</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Report is posted as a comment directly on the PR. It updates on each push — you always see the latest results without leaving the PR page.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Step Summary</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Same report is written to GitHub Actions step summary. Every build is preserved in the Actions history for long-term reference.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Failure Details</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Failed tests are listed with their error messages directly in the report. No need to dig through CI logs to find what broke.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Downloadable Artifacts</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Full HTML test report, interactive coverage map, JUnit XML, and security scan results available as downloadable artifacts for 30 days.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- REVIEW GATES -->
  <section id="reviews" class="section">
    <h2 class="text-[28px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-white">Review <span class="text-teal-300">Gates</span></h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-9 max-w-[620px]">Every PR requires two independent reviews before merge. Code quality and test quality are reviewed separately by different roles.</p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5 mb-8">
      <div class="card !border-teal-400/30">
        <div class="text-[10px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-teal-400 font-semibold mb-3">Gate 1</div>
        <div class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3">Dev Lead Review</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
          <ul class="list-none flex flex-col gap-2 p-0">
            <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="text-teal-400">&#9679;</span> Code follows project conventions and style</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="text-teal-400">&#9679;</span> Architecture and design are sound</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="text-teal-400">&#9679;</span> No unnecessary complexity or over-engineering</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="text-teal-400">&#9679;</span> Error handling is appropriate</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="text-teal-400">&#9679;</span> Logging follows the standard</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="text-teal-400">&#9679;</span> No security concerns</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card !border-green-400/30">
        <div class="text-[10px] tracking-[0.2em] uppercase text-green-400 font-semibold mb-3">Gate 2</div>
        <div class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-3">QA Lead Review</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
          <ul class="list-none flex flex-col gap-2 p-0">
            <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="text-green-400">&#9679;</span> Tests cover the right scenarios (happy path, errors, edges)</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="text-green-400">&#9679;</span> Tests are meaningful — not testing trivial code</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="text-green-400">&#9679;</span> Test names clearly describe what they verify</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="text-green-400">&#9679;</span> Coverage has not dropped below 80%</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="text-green-400">&#9679;</span> No flaky or environment-dependent tests</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2 items-start"><span class="text-green-400">&#9679;</span> Regression tests updated if behavior changed</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="diagram-box max-w-[650px]">
      <div class="text-[12px] text-teal-400 font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-4">Review Flow</div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 text-[13px] flex-wrap">
        <span class="text-purple-400 font-mono">PR Created</span>
        <span class="text-gray-500">&rarr;</span>
        <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono">CI Passes</span>
        <span class="text-gray-500">&rarr;</span>
        <span class="text-teal-300 font-mono">Dev Lead Review</span>
        <span class="text-gray-500">&rarr;</span>
        <span class="text-green-400 font-mono">QA Lead Review</span>
        <span class="text-gray-500">&rarr;</span>
        <span class="text-white font-mono">Merge</span>
      </div>
      <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-3.5">Both reviews must be completed and signed off in the PR template before merge. Neither is optional.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- NOTIFICATIONS -->
  <section id="notify" class="section">
    <h2 class="text-[28px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-white">Build <span class="text-teal-300">Notifications</span></h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-9 max-w-[620px]">Every build sends a notification to Slack. Color-coded, with direct links. No news is not good news — you should always know what happened.</p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-7">
      <div class="card !border-l-[3px] !border-l-green-400">
        <div class="text-[13px] font-semibold text-green-400 mb-2">Pass Notification</div>
        <div class="bg-gray-800/50 rounded-lg p-3.5 text-xs leading-7">
          <div class="text-green-400">&#10003; <strong class="text-gray-100">PR #42: Add audio extraction step</strong></div>
          <div class="text-gray-500">All checks passed</div>
          <div class="text-gray-500 text-[11px] italic">briborg &middot; imi-library &middot; 14:32 UTC</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card !border-l-[3px] !border-l-red-400">
        <div class="text-[13px] font-semibold text-red-400 mb-2">Fail Notification</div>
        <div class="bg-gray-800/50 rounded-lg p-3.5 text-xs leading-7">
          <div class="text-red-400">&#10007; <strong class="text-gray-100">PR #43: Update transcription config</strong></div>
          <div class="text-gray-500">Failed: test, security</div>
          <div class="text-gray-500 text-[11px] italic">briborg &middot; imi-library &middot; 15:07 UTC</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="diagram-box max-w-[600px]">
      <div class="text-[12px] text-teal-400 font-semibold tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-3.5">When Notifications Fire</div>
      <table class="w-full text-[13px]">
        <tr class="border-b border-teal-400/15">
          <td class="py-2 text-gray-100 font-medium">PR opened / updated</td>
          <td class="py-2 text-gray-500">CI result + PR link + author</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-teal-400/15">
          <td class="py-2 text-gray-100 font-medium">Push to dev</td>
          <td class="py-2 text-gray-500">CI result + commit link + author</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-b border-teal-400/15">
          <td class="py-2 text-gray-100 font-medium">Push to staging</td>
          <td class="py-2 text-gray-500">CI result + commit link + author</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="py-2 text-gray-100 font-medium">Push to main</td>
          <td class="py-2 text-gray-500">Deploy notice + commit link + author</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-6 max-w-[600px]">
      <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-2.5">How to Activate</div>
      <div class="flow">
        <div class="flow-step mini">
          <div class="flow-num mini">1</div>
          <div class="flow-body mini">
            <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-100">Create a Slack incoming webhook (Apps &rarr; Incoming Webhooks &rarr; Add to channel)</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-step mini">
          <div class="flow-num mini">2</div>
          <div class="flow-body mini">
            <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-100">Add webhook URL as a GitHub Actions secret: <code class="text-teal-400 text-xs">SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL</code></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-step">
          <div class="flow-num mini">3</div>
          <div class="flow-body mini">
            <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-100">Done — notifications start automatically on the next CI run</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-3">The notification job is pre-wired in CI from setup.sh. It skips gracefully if the secret isn't set — nothing breaks.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DEFINITION OF DONE -->
  <section id="dod" class="section">
    <h2 class="text-[28px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-white">Definition of <span class="text-teal-300">Done</span></h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-9 max-w-[620px]">A feature is complete when every box is checked. Not before.</p>

    <ul class="checklist">
      <li><span class="check-box">&#10003;</span>Code is written and follows project conventions (black, ruff clean)</li>
      <li><span class="check-box">&#10003;</span>Unit tests + integration tests included in the same PR</li>
      <li><span class="check-box">&#10003;</span>All tests pass locally (<code class="text-teal-400 text-[13px]">pytest -v</code>)</li>
      <li><span class="check-box">&#10003;</span>Coverage has not dropped below 80%</li>
      <li><span class="check-box">&#10003;</span>PR description follows the template (what, why, how to test, checklist)</li>
      <li><span class="check-box">&#10003;</span>CI passes — lint + test + security scan</li>
      <li><span class="check-box">&#10003;</span>Build report shows no regressions</li>
      <li><span class="check-box">&#10003;</span>Dev Lead has reviewed and approved (code quality)</li>
      <li><span class="check-box">&#10003;</span>QA Lead has reviewed and approved (test quality)</li>
      <li><span class="check-box">&#10003;</span>CHANGELOG.md is updated</li>
      <li><span class="check-box">&#10003;</span>PR is reviewed and merged via GitHub</li>
      <li><span class="check-box">&#10003;</span>Linked requirement or issue is updated or closed</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- FULL TOOLBOX -->
  <section id="toolbox" class="section">
    <h2 class="text-[28px] font-bold mb-1.5 text-white">Full <span class="text-teal-300">Toolbox</span></h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-9 max-w-[620px]">Everything that ships with the project template. One setup script installs all of it.</p>

    <div class="cards-grid">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3">&#9881;</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Git Configuration</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed"><code class="text-teal-400 text-[11px]">fetch.prune = true</code> auto-cleans stale remote refs. <code class="text-teal-400 text-[11px]">git-done</code> alias for post-merge cleanup.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3">&#9878;</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">GitHub Actions CI</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Auto-detects Python, Node, or full-stack. Generates <code class="text-teal-400 text-[11px]">ci.yml</code> with lint + test + security. Triggers on main/dev/staging.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3">&#128274;</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Pre-commit Hooks</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">9 hooks: formatting (black), linting (ruff), secret detection, large file guard, YAML validation, merge conflict check.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3">&#128196;</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">PR Template</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Standardized PR format: what changed, why, how to test, checklist. Auto-fills on every new PR.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3">&#128209;</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">ADR Template</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Architecture Decision Records in <code class="text-teal-400 text-[11px]">docs/decisions/</code>. Context, options, decision, consequences.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3">&#128300;</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Dependabot</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Weekly checks for pip + GitHub Actions dependency updates. Opens PRs automatically with "dependencies" label.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3">&#128221;</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">CHANGELOG.md</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Keep a Changelog format with semantic versioning. Updated in every PR that changes behavior.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3">&#128269;</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Security Scanning</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">detect-secrets (leaked keys), pip-audit (dependency CVEs), bandit (Python code security). All in CI.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3">&#128200;</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Test Reports</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">HTML test report, interactive coverage map, JUnit XML for PR summaries. 30-day artifact retention.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3">&#128203;</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Logging Standard</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Python <code class="text-teal-400 text-[11px]">logging</code> module only. DEBUG / INFO / WARNING / ERROR. Always include context.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3">&#128230;</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">pyproject.toml</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Centralized config for black, ruff, and pytest. Coverage threshold, HTML reports, JUnit XML all pre-configured.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <div class="text-[22px] mb-3">&#128462;</div>
        <div class="text-[15px] font-semibold text-white mb-1.5">Deliverables</div>
        <div class="text-[13px] text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Every HTML doc also saved as PDF (Chrome headless). PDF is the shareable format for Drive and external teams.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FOOTER -->
  <footer class="mt-16 py-12 border-t border-gray-800">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-2 text-xs text-gray-500 tracking-wide">
      <span>Brian Borg's Dev Process Template</span>
      <span>Last updated March 2026</span>
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>

